{
  "topic_description": "A pseudo-element is like adding or targeting an extra element without having to add more HTML. They have a variety of roles and you can learn about them in this module.",
  "topic": [
    {
      "title": "::before and ::after",
      "description": "Both the ::before and ::after pseudo-elements create a child element inside an element only if you define a content property. In CSS, ::after creates a pseudo-element that is the last child of the selected element. It is often used to add cosmetic content to an element with the content property. It is inline by default. In CSS, ::before creates a pseudo-element that is the first child of the selected element. It is often used to add cosmetic content to an element with the content property. It is inline by default.",
